The paper deals with mechanism design, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). It also involves the design of algorithms for auctions and matching markets, which falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of distributions and Bayesian optimization, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG). The analysis of envy-free outcomes and the comparison with incentive-compatible mechanisms are related to decision making and optimization (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with economic theory and market design, which is a subfield of computational economics (cs.EC).
